##How effective is the large-scale online teaching at present? We did a little research

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

By Chae Rim, _ thepaper.cn _

From years ago to years later, Ali's office software "nail" download experienced a roller coaster-like ups and downs.

As a corporate mobile office application, nail the daily download of years ago in Apple's APP Store between the top 50 and 20. However, surprisingly, after the festival on February 4, nail hit the top of the APP Store download list, and consecutive "top list" so far this month.

Nail developers may not have thought, in addition to the top, nail also received more than 820,000 of the 1 star rating. One-star reviews are filled with students'resentment and resentment of the relentless deprivation of their long winter vacation lives.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Around February 10, negative ratings began to spike. On this day, it is the time when many primary and secondary schools begin to teach online courses. In addition to negative reviews on the APP store platform, "Student Party" on the B site to produce a spoof video, vent their grievances.

The Internet course, from the Ministry of Education, "No suspension of classes, no suspension" policy. During the outbreak, schools and colleges across the country issued a notice to delay the official return to school; online courses have become one of the many schools.

What is the actual implementation of online teaching at present? What are the real views of students, teachers and parents hidden behind the complaints and practical jokes? Based on these questions, the paper's online questionnaire * , which was distributed using the www.thepaper.cn  platform, surveyed nearly 1,000 students, parents and teachers at all levels to try to outline the general effect of this massive online education.

01

What is the original intention of the policy of "suspension without suspension" ?

01

What is the original intention of the policy of "suspension without suspension" ?

February 27, the Central Working Leadership Group Meeting to deal with the epidemic of new pneumonia stressed that universities, primary and secondary schools, kindergartens and other start-up time in principle continue to delay. As of February 28, there is still no clear date for the official back-to-school starting date in all provinces except Guizhou Province, the third year of Senior High School, and the Third Year of junior high school. However, many provincial and municipal education departments have started to deploy online teaching.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
More than 90 percent of college students, teachers and parents of primary and middle school students said online teaching activities had begun on Feb. 26, thepaper.cn found in a survey. The vast majority of students take the course by participating in live online courses, and about two thirds of parents of primary and secondary school students say their child has started compulsory education.

"The large-scale live online lecture is the largest experiment in the history of human education in 40 years, " Liu Dehuan, a professor at Peking University, said of the current online education on his personal account. However, a careful review of the ministry's recent policy shows that "no suspension" does not mean forcing all teachers to appear on camera, simply live-streaming classes; nor does it mean starting new classes early.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On February 5, the Ministry of Education issued a notice saying that "primary and secondary schools will not start online teaching of the new semester courses before the official opening day planned in various places, " and many regions have responded to the notice, it has been stipulated that no new course teaching will be carried out before the formal start of primary and secondary schools. The Ministry of Education said only that it would "ensure the progress and quality of teaching" .

For Primary and secondary schools, the Ministry of Education issued the policy "original intention" is that even online teaching, primary and secondary schools at all levels can use the "national network cloud classroom" and other existing resources to teach. For remote rural areas without internet or with slow speed, the Ministry of Education will arrange for China Education Television to broadcast relevant courses and resources to solve the problem of students studying at home in these areas.

In reality, it is still difficult to implement the measure of "no suspension of classes and no suspension of studies" in rural areas. On Feb. 14, thepaper.cn reported that a girl in Yichang, Hubei Province, was returning to her hometown in the mountains for the Lunar New Year So the girl's grandfather built a "mountain classroom" for her on the mountain with bamboo poles and tarps where the signal was steady. In response, Sichuan online comments, rural areas how to solve the "suspension without suspension" problem, it is clear that all parties need to be more serious.

02

Nail and tencent classrooms were the most widely used platforms in the survey

02

Nail and tencent classrooms were the most widely used platforms in the survey

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At present, many online teaching platforms are mentioned in the online teaching plans of provincial and municipal education departments and universities. Many of the university's designated teaching platforms include superstar learning, rain classes, and moocs at Chinese universities. Primary and Secondary School Teaching Platform including local cable TV / IPTV, as well as a variety of national (such as "national network cloud classroom") , provincial teaching platform.

Most of the "classes without suspension" program, are not mentioned in the use of nails, Wechat, QQ and other social communication and office software to teach. According to the survey, both the education sector and universities'designated teaching platforms are less popular than market-based Internet company software.

During the investigation, the reporter learned that due to the Internet, many teachers have a backup plan for the platform outside the designated teaching platform, which is usually due to the collapse of Cottonwood, the school's designated teaching platform (such as Super Star learning pass, rain class) , google has had to switch to more stable platforms; universities have pushed to use platforms such as rain classes, mostly because they can monitor teachers'attendance online.

03

The teaching time has been reduced and most teachers'preparation time has increased

03

The teaching time has been reduced and most teachers'preparation time has increased

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At present, the school time and frequency of students in universities, middle schools and primary schools have been significantly reduced. Questionnaire statistics show that the majority of primary and secondary school students receive courses in the daily length of between 2-3 hours, university students receive courses in the daily length of between 2-4 hours. Most students only use the Internet for 3-4 classes a day.

At present, many education departments, but also clearly defined the primary and secondary school students to accept the maximum time limit for online classes. As stipulated in the plan promulgated by Chongqing Municipality, in principle, primary and secondary schools shall adopt a half-day teaching system, which shall not exceed four school hours per day, 15 minutes per class hour for teachers in primary schools and 20 minutes in secondary schools.

Students seemed relaxed, but 71 percent of teachers polled said online class preparation was more time-consuming than offline class preparation. Many teachers believe that preparing lesson plans and familiarizing themselves with the live platform and hardware will increase their preparation time.

04

Outside of the Cottonwood platform, communication and interaction become a short board for online teaching

04

Outside of the Cottonwood platform, communication and interaction become a short board for online teaching

Recently, public opinion continues to discuss "online teaching platform collapse" this phenomenon. However, according to the survey, the platform Cottonwood crash is not the biggest problem that students and teachers face in online teaching.

Both students and teachers, the common problem reflected in the questionnaire is that communication and interaction can not be guaranteed in the online education process. "What is more painful in class is not seeing the students' expressions and feedback, which is a one-man show, " a teacher told The Paper.

The different parties who play different roles in online teaching have different problems. In the eyes of parents of primary and secondary school students, they are more worried about their children's nearsightedness, fatigue and psychological weariness of online teaching courses, can Not effectively monitor the completion of students'homework in class and after class.

05

Parents and teachers of primary and secondary school students have low acceptance of online education

05

Parents and teachers of primary and secondary school students have low acceptance of online education

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
According to the results of the questionnaire, college students have a high acceptance of online education.

Elementary and middle school students and teachers at all levels are less receptive and would like to resume offline teaching as soon as possible. A large proportion of respondents also believe that online education is a "very good learning model. ".

More than two-thirds of college students surveyed self-rated the effectiveness of their online education as very good, only about 5 percent of those surveyed said online education was "poor" or "very poor. ".

However, in interviews, some university teachers expressed their concerns about the effectiveness of online education, in addition to the inability to communicate effectively with students; "I don't know if students are submitting their homework online after class, if they are copying each other, or if the students sitting in front of the camera at the other end of the computer are actually paying attention. "

* Note:

1. The questionnaire was distributed at noon on February 26 and was collected in the evening of February 26. After screening, a total of 858 questionnaires covering college students, parents of primary and secondary school students and teachers at all levels were obtained from all parts of the country, the response rate was 95.3% (400 questionnaires were sent to college students, 300 to parents and 200 to teachers) . The pity of this paper is that the number of samples is small and the final results are for reference only.

The three questionnaires are linked to:

A questionnaire for teachers: https://www.credamo.com/answer.html/s/1uy  
Questionnaire for parents of primary and secondary school students: https://www.credamo.com/answer.html/s/1uu
